Prefer borrowing or single ownership:

```rust
// Good: Use Box for owned children
struct Node {
    value: i32,
    children: Vec<Box<Node>>,
}

// Or borrow when possible
fn process_nodes(nodes: &[Node]) {
    // Work with borrowed references
}
```

notes:
Translating every `shared_ptr` to `Rc`/`Arc`.

```rust
// Bad: Unnecessary shared ownership
use std::rc::Rc;

struct Node {
    value: i32,
    children: Vec<Rc<Node>>,  // Over-engineered
}
```

target_pattern:
```rust
// Return owned value instead:
fn get_data() -> Data {
    Data::new()
}

// Or use Box for heap allocation:
fn get_data() -> Box<Data> {
    Box::new(Data::new())
}
```

notes:
